eme_(TV_series)#Recurring_cast|Linh]], the fictitious Vietnamese-American woman played by [[Hong Chau]], whom [[Treme_(TV_series)#Cast_and_characters|Sonny]] courts then marries, in the HBO TV series ''[[Treme (TV series)|Treme]]''<ref>{{cite news|author=Walker, Dave|work=The Times-Picayune|location=New Orleans|title= Actress Hong Chau brings New Orleans background to role as 'Treme's' Linh|date=November 18, 2012| url=https://www.nola.com/treme-hbo/2012/11/actress_hong_chau_brings_new_o.html}}</ref>\n* [[Linh Dinh]] (Vietnamese \u0110inh Linh, born 1963) Vietnamese-American poet, fiction writer, translator, and photographer\n* [[Ch\u1ebf Linh]], Vietnamese pop singer of Cham origin\n\n==See also==\n* [[Ling (surname)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{given name|type=both}}\n\n[[Category:Vietnamese-language surnames]]\n", "name_user": "Lives4Christ", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linh"}
{"title_page": "Sunico Films", "text_new": "'''Sunico Productions''' is a company founded by Denmark-based [[India|Indian]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sindhishaan.com/article/personalities/pers_06_02c.html|title=Sindhishaan - Mangharam Harwani|website=www.sindhishaan.com|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref> businessman Mangharam Harwani to preserve [[Sindhi people|Sindhi]] culture, language, and traditions through film.<ref name=\"Economic Times\">{{cite news|last1=Mulchandani|first1=Leena|title=Sindhi film industry striving hard to revive fading culture|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2009-07-11/news/28488245_1_sindhis-film-laxman-bhatia|accessdate=1 February 2015|publisher=[[The Economic Times]]|date=11 June 2009}}</ref>  Sunico produces [[Sindhi language]] films, and was the first production house to launch a Sindhi film after a gap of 5 years.<ref name=\"One India\">{{cite news|last1=staff|title=Sindhi film launched after 5 years|url=http://www.oneindia.com/2007/08/19/sindhi-film-launched-after-5-years-1187505127.html|accessdate=1 February 2015|publisher=[[One India]]|date=19 August 2007}}</ref> Sunico also sells online CDs and DVDs of its films and provides streaming facilities for viewing their movies online, and is considered \"one of the leading suppliers in Denmark\".<ref name=Sindhishaan>{{cite news|last1=staff|title=GLOBAL INDIAN ORIGIN AWARD 2012|url=http://www.sindhishaan.com/article/personalities/pers_11_02e.html|accessdate=1 February 2015|work=Volume  11|issue=2|publisher=Sindhishaan|date=June 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Films==\n* ''[[Pyar Ka Tarana]]'' (1993) (written and directed by [[Dev Anand]])\n* ''[[Pyar Kare Dis : Feel The Power of Love]]'' (2007)\n\n==Directors==\nThe following directors have worked under the Sunico banner:\n\n* Kamal Nathani \u2013 ''[[Pyar Kare Dis : Feel The Power of Love]]'' (2007)\n* [[Dev Anand]] \u2013 ''[[Pyar Ka Tarana]]'' (1993)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20130625052221/http://sunicofilms.com/ Official Site]\n* {{DNFc|143809}}\n* [https://www.imdb.com/company/co0130958/ Sunico Productions] at the [[Internet Movie Database]]\n\n[[Category:Film production companies of Denmark]]\n\n{{film-company-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Sunico Productions''' is a company founded by Denmark-based [[People of Pakistan|Pakistani]] businessman Mangharam Harwani to preserve [[Sindhi people|Sindhi]] culture, language, and traditions through film.<ref name=\"Economic Times\">{{cite news|last1=Mulchandani|first1=Leena|title=Sindhi film industry striving hard to revive fading culture|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2009-07-11/news/28488245_1_sindhis-film-laxman-bhatia|accessdate=1 February 2015|publisher=[[The Economic Times]]|date=11 June 2009}}</ref>  Sunico produces [[Sindhi language]] films, and was the first production house to launch a Sindhi film after a gap of 5 years.<ref name=\"One India\">{{cite news|last1=staff|title=Sindhi film launched after 5 years|url=http://www.oneindia.com/2007/08/19/sindhi-film-launched-after-5-years-1187505127.html|accessdate=1 February 2015|publisher=[[One India]]|date=19 August 2007}}</ref> Sunico also sells online CDs and DVDs of its films and provides streaming facilities for viewing their movies online, and is considered \"one of the leading suppliers in Denmark\".<ref name=Sindhishaan>{{cite news|last1=staff|title=GLOBAL INDIAN ORIGIN AWARD 2012|url=http://www.sindhishaan.com/article/personalities/pers_11_02e.html|accessdate=1 February 2015|work=Volume  11|issue=2|publisher=Sindhishaan|date=June 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Films==\n* ''[[Pyar Ka Tarana]]'' (1993) (written and directed by [[Dev Anand]])\n* ''[[Pyar Kare Dis : Feel The Power of Love]]'' (2007)\n\n==Directors==\nThe following directors have worked under the Sunico banner:\n\n* Kamal Nathani \u2013 ''[[Pyar Kare Dis : Feel The Power of Love]]'' (2007)\n* [[Dev Anand]] \u2013 ''[[Pyar Ka Tarana]]'' (1993)\n\n==References==\n{{ref